{"questionId":"15304001","questionHtml":"<p>By considering&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></munder><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></math>, show that, for all finite&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></munder><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, (hence&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>as<em><strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>and so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></munder><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: The<em><strong> R1</strong></em> is dependent on the<em><strong>&nbsp;M1.</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>uses either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;to form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;and so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>→</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></munder><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>The<strong>&nbsp;R1&nbsp;</strong>is dependent on the<strong>&nbsp;M1.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15304001","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By considering limα→π2tan α, show that, for all finite fx, y, limα→π2gx, y=-1fx, y.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.13—Limits and L’Hopitals"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}